{"claim_id": "claim_008", "text": "The molecular network was precomputed on the GNPS website and extracted in GraphML format.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "the molecular network has been precomputed on the GNPS website and extracted in the *GraphML* format (file *pnordicum_ms2_gnps.graphml* inside the *dataset* subdirectory of the *mineMS2* installation folder).", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_minems2/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [1092, 1291], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "data", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000006", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": {"context": "Penicillium nordicum analysis workflow", "subject": "molecular network", "qualifier": "has_property", "relation": "precomputed on GNPS and extracted in GraphML format", "object": "pnordicum_ms2_gnps.graphml file"}, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["SYS_MINEMS2", "TOOL_GNPS"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_027", "text": "The findGNPSComponents function extracts connected components from the molecular network.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "We consider 3 type of components of the network:\n\n-   the **connected components** of the graph (subgraphs in which any two nodes are connected by a path)", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_minems2/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [5077, 5231], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": {"context": "GNPS network component extraction", "subject": "connected components", "qualifier": "is_a", "relation": "subgraphs with connected nodes", "object": "network connectivity patterns"}, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["COMP_FINDGNPS"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_028", "text": "The findGNPSComponents function can extract cliques from the molecular network.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "-   the **cliques** (subgraphs in which any all pairs of nodes are connected)", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_minems2/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [5233, 5310], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": {"context": "GNPS network component extraction", "subject": "cliques", "qualifier": "is_a", "relation": "subgraphs with fully connected node pairs", "object": "fully connected network substructures"}, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["COMP_FINDGNPS"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_029", "text": "The findGNPSComponents function selects a set of disjoint cliques by decreasing order of size.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "Instead of computing all the cliques from the network, **mineMS2 selects a set of disjoint cliques** (i.e. cliques without any nodes in common) by decreasing number of size (nodes): the algorithm starts with the biggest clique, then searches for the biggest clique that does not contain any node of this first clique, and so on until no clique is left", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_minems2/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [2444, 2754], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": {"context": "GNPS clique extraction algorithm", "subject": "mineMS2 clique selection", "qualifier": "has_property", "relation": "selects disjoint cliques in decreasing size order", "object": "computationally efficient clique representation"}, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["SYS_MINEMS2", "COMP_FINDGNPS"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_030", "text": "The findGNPSComponents function can extract high similarity pairs of nodes from the molecular network.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "-   the **high similarity pairs of nodes** (pairs of spectra with a cosine score superior to a threshold)", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_minems2/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [5669, 5774], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": {"context": "GNPS network component extraction", "subject": "high similarity pairs", "qualifier": "is_a", "relation": "spectrum pairs with cosine score above threshold", "object": "spectral similarity relationships"}, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["COMP_FINDGNPS"]}
{"claim_id": "claim_031", "text": "The minSize parameter of findGNPSComponents specifies the minimum size of detected cliques.", "claim_type": "explicit", "source_excerpt": "**All these components can be extracted** using the **`findGNPSComponents`** function, with the main parameters:\n\n1\\.\n`minSize`: minimum size of the detected cliques", "source_anchor": {"source_path": "/Users/nothiasl/git/AgenticScienceBuilder/outputs/asbb_pilot/coll_minems2/synthesized_package", "source_section": "intro", "page": null, "char_span": [5863, 6028], "figure_id": null, "table_id": null}, "source_type": "text", "evidence_type": "knowledge", "trace_status": "exact_match", "evidence_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302", "source_type_uri": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000311", "super_pattern": {"context": "findGNPSComponents parameter specification", "subject": "minSize parameter", "qualifier": "has_property", "relation": "controls minimum clique size threshold", "object": "clique size filtering"}, "source_doi": null, "spine_entity_ids": ["COMP_FINDGNPS"]}
